======================================================================
SECTION 2: IS H A FUNCTION OF SPECTRAL POWER SUMS?
======================================================================

    If H depends only on the eigenvalue magnitudes |lambda_k|, then it is
    determined by the power sums sigma_j = sum_k y_k^{2j} (j=1,2,...).
    Test: do tournaments with same (sigma_1, sigma_2, ...) have same H?

  p=5: 1 power sum(s) → 1 signatures, 1 distinct H values. Determined: True
  p=5: 2 power sum(s) → 1 signatures, 1 distinct H values. Determined: True
  p=5: 3 power sum(s) → 1 signatures, 1 distinct H values. Determined: True
  p=5: 4 power sum(s) → 1 signatures, 1 distinct H values. Determined: True
  p=7: 1 power sum(s) → 1 signatures, 2 distinct H values. Determined: False
  p=7: 2 power sum(s) → 2 signatures, 2 distinct H values. Determined: True
  p=7: 3 power sum(s) → 2 signatures, 2 distinct H values. Determined: True
  p=7: 4 power sum(s) → 2 signatures, 2 distinct H values. Determined: True
  p=11: 1 power sum(s) → 1 signatures, 4 distinct H values. Determined: False
  p=11: 2 power sum(s) → 4 signatures, 4 distinct H values. Determined: True
  p=11: 3 power sum(s) → 4 signatures, 4 distinct H values. Determined: True
